

Arrow is an American television series developed by Greg Berlanti, Marc Guggenheim, and Andrew Kreisberg based on the DC Comics character Green Arrow. The series follows the adventures of billionaire playboy Oliver Queen (Stephen Amell) as he becomes the vigilante known as the Green Arrow. The series debuted on October 10, 2012, on The CW and has since gone on to become one of the network's most watched and acclaimed shows.

The series follows Oliver Queen, a billionaire playboy who returns home to Starling City after being stranded on a deserted island for five years. When he returns, he finds that the city has been taken over by criminals and corrupt businessmen. In order to protect his city, Oliver takes on the mantle of the Green Arrow and begins to fight crime. He is aided by his team, which includes his bodyguard John Diggle (David Ramsey), tech genius Felicity Smoak (Emily Bett Rickards), and his sister Thea Queen (Willa Holland).

The series is known for its complex storylines and action sequences. Each season typically follows a different story arc, with Oliver facing off against a variety of villains. The show has featured a wide range of characters from the DC Comics universe, including Deathstroke, Ra's al Ghul, and Malcolm Merlyn.

The show has been praised for its strong female characters, with Felicity Smoak and Laurel Lance (Katie Cassidy) being two of the show's most popular characters. The show has also been praised for its strong LGBT representation, with the character of Nyssa al Ghul (Katrina Law) being a bisexual character.

The show has been a ratings success for The CW, with its seventh and final season being the highest rated in its history. It has also been nominated for several awards, including a Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Special Visual Effects.

Overall, Arrow has been a success for The CW and has become a fan favorite. The show has featured a wide range of characters, action sequences, and storylines that have kept viewers coming back for more. With its final season now airing, Arrow will go down as one of the most successful series in The CW's history.